d form of Gaelic <b>Ó Cearbhaill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cearbhall</i>’ (see   Carroll  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Carroll","meanings":["Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Cearbhaill</b> or <b>Mac Cearbhaill</b> ‘descendant (or son) of <i>Cearbhall</i>’, a personal name perhaps based on <i>cearbh</i> ‘hacking’ and hence originally a byname for a butcher or a fierce warrior.","English and Scottish: variant of   Carrell  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Prince Maelruana O\"Carroll of Éile was born in 1382, in Wicklow, County Wicklow, Ireland, his father, Sir Tiege O Carrol Ó Cearbhaill King of Ely, was 30 and his mother, Joan Boteler, was 22. He married Catherine Kate O'Reilly in 1414, in Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1423, in Powerstown, County Kilkenny, Ireland, at the age of 41, and was buried in Clonmacnoise, County Offaly, Ireland."},"et":{"1382–1423":"1382–1423","1380–1451":"1380–1451","1390–1480":"1390–1480","1392–1451":"1392–1451","–1464":"–1464","1395–1422":"1395–1422","1385–Female":"1385–Surnud","1415–1506":"1415–1506","1352–1407":"1352–1407","1360–1392":"1360–1392","7 November 1392":"7. november 1392","1352":"1352","1385":"1385","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1392":"1392","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1415":"1415","1414":"1414","1423":"1423","1422":"1422","1464":"1464","1407":"1407","1506":"1506","Clonmacnoise Cemetery Clonmacnoise, County Offaly, Ireland":"Clonmacnoise, County Offaly, Iirimaa","Clonmacnoise, Offaly, Ireland":"Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Iirimaa","County Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Iirimaa","Knockt Castle, Wicklow, Ireland":"Wicklow, County Wicklow, Iirimaa","Polestown, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Powerstown, County Kilkenny, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1382–1423":"1382–1423","1380–1451":"1380–1451","1390–1480":"1390–1480","1392–1451":"1392–1451","–1464":"–1464","1395–1422":"1395–1422","1385–Female":"1385–Kuollut","1415–1506":"1415–1506","1352–1407":"1352